3. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper deals with denial constraints, which are a type of logical constraint. The use of disjunctive databases also falls under the scope of logic in computer science.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may involve discussions on the computational complexity of computing the canonical disjunctive database or the size of the database.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The proposed algorithm for computing the canonical disjunctive database may involve data structures and algorithms.
